The survival of the rhino is under threat. That is according to the World Wildlife Fund, which says that more than 8 000 rhinos have been poached for their horns since 2010. They are killed to meet the high demand for horns in Asia. But in South Africa, the staff at a wildlife reserve say they have found a way to try and save the species. Anti-poaching technology to expand globally in bid to save wildlife Technology that has dramatically reduced rhino poaching in a South African game reserve could be used to help other threatened species across the world, as conservationists look for new ways to stop poachers before they can reach wildlife. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24Â on Twitter  